@BlackhaloZ nah, the live action is absolute trash.
I wanted to puke and laugh at the same time during the entire Mihawk vs Zoro fight...
It's a fan-made mediocrity from untalented fans trying to act.

@marvinericdelosreyes 😅 I’m sorry, there are plenty of actors that took roles that ended up destroying their careers. There are plenty of actors that only take roles that align with their values. There’s even actors that refuse to take roles
If they’re required to take off any clothes or kiss other people because they’re married. I won’t be surprised if this torches Liam. The teaser looks awful and the brief dialogue we heard sounded worse. I wish him luck, I’m not watching. 

And, the point of watching is seeing something you imagined come alive. That’s like asking why go to a theme park that’s made after Hogwarts. So you can physically see and/or touch it.

@michaelh9649 Right? What a crazy take. What’s the point of taking over an IP if you’re going to change everything? Obviously there are some thing’s that might be different when adapting to the big screen, but if you change the whole point of an IP, you’re likely to loose the very people that made it popular to begin with. 

They turned this show into a series for man haters. I can’t think of who else this is for. The only reason I can see for benching Geralt in his own show is you hate men - just like what Kathleen Kennedy did with Star Wars. 

Normal women who appreciate men don’t like seeing this treatment of amazing male characters either. Awful.
